❌ Rejected the contribution.
Comment: I feel like this takes too long to solve and is too complex. I hope the best and take care.

Goal
* Consider deleting "Wait... are we missing some information here?"

* Consider changing "two shots" and "every shot" to "two points" and "every point", as it's not clear that one shot corresponds to one point.

* In the last paragraph, "the serving player" could be misunderstood as "the first serving player". Please change "the serving player's score is always announced in front. When" to:

the score of the player <<who will serve next>> is always announced <<first>>. If the set has already ended, this still applies hypothetically: the first score announced is the score of the player who would serve next if the game were to continue. For example, when

Output
* Consider separating the possible outputs into different lines for clarity:

<<Line 1:>> One of the following:
 • {{LEADER IS}}, followed by the name of the player who leads the set, or
 • {{TIE}} if both players have the same score, or
 • the name of the player who won, followed by {{WON!!!}}.
<<Line 2:>> One of the following:
 • {{SERVER IS}} and the name of the player who is going to serve if the set is not ended, or
 • {{SET ENDED}} otherwise.

Stub generator
* Line 1: Please change to:
read playerA:word(10) playerB:word(10)

Thanks.
Updated inputs, thanks for your advice !

Should there be some improvements in the goal section to make it a bit easier ?
By the way, I don't think it would be harder than some current CoC ...
